- As a guest here--

00:44:18.530 --> 00:44:20.570
I feel myself very
much as a guest

00:44:20.570 --> 00:44:21.860
in this beautiful country--

00:44:21.860 --> 00:44:24.670
I've worked so long with
many colleagues in the US,

00:44:24.670 --> 00:44:28.220
I am not going to say anything
very specific on the US.

00:44:28.220 --> 00:44:31.250
I think my US colleagues
should do this.

00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:34.940
But yes, I think
prevention is, in nearly

00:44:34.940 --> 00:44:40.730
every respect in medicine, in
disease, is the way forward.

00:44:40.730 --> 00:44:42.255
And do we do enough?

00:44:46.850 --> 00:44:49.626
You won't, you know.

00:44:49.626 --> 00:44:51.690
I have to apologize, but indeed.

00:44:51.690 --> 00:44:53.130
We do not, overall.

00:44:53.130 --> 00:44:54.330
We do not do enough.

00:44:54.330 --> 00:44:58.770
We could, by and
large, I think, if we

00:44:58.770 --> 00:45:01.410
would have sufficient
preventive measures,

00:45:01.410 --> 00:45:05.940
eradicate, with really strong
efforts worldwide, nearly

00:45:05.940 --> 00:45:09.070
all catastrophic
infectious diseases.

00:45:09.070 --> 00:45:11.070
I think there is no
reason to believe

00:45:11.070 --> 00:45:12.520
that we could not do that.

00:45:12.520 --> 00:45:14.280
I'm not talking
about Alzheimer now.

00:45:14.280 --> 00:45:20.010
If we would have even stronger
emphasis on prevention

00:45:20.010 --> 00:45:22.980
in heart disease,
cardiovascular disease,

00:45:22.980 --> 00:45:27.110
we could at least
reduce it with half.

00:45:27.110 --> 00:45:30.360
I am quoting now again
Richard Peto from Oxford--

00:45:30.360 --> 00:45:31.410
just retired--

00:45:31.410 --> 00:45:35.590
but he always goes around
that we can basically prevent

00:45:35.590 --> 00:45:38.530
about 50% of early mortalities.

00:45:38.530 --> 00:45:42.850
So in that sense, prevention,
yes, we could do much more.

00:45:45.400 --> 00:45:47.170
I missed your second
question but--

00:45:50.170 --> 00:45:55.190
- Your opinion about what is
known as the Bredesen Protocols

00:45:55.190 --> 00:46:01.456
